        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2018-03-16 04:19:07.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\npython-version still needs to be defined also you dont need to define it for each subproject, just along with the other variables after line 6. Here is an example of how other projects do it: ci-management/jjb/dcaegen2/dcaegen2-utils.yaml\n\nOne more observation, the python-version is used in the virtualenv command:\nvirtualenv --quiet -p \"$PYTHON_VERSION\" \"/tmp/v/tox\"\nWhich only supports either 'python2' or 'python3', but not both. \n\nFor running tox, does your team runs this in a python2 env? This is the most common.",
        "patchset_number": 3
      },
